The paper deals with text generation and information extraction, which are both common topics in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a joint neural model for both tasks, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The experiments involve knowledge graphs from Visual Genome, which is related to computer vision, and thus cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with structured data, which is a common topic in information retrieval, and thus cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible sub-category.
